.TH start-cli-backup 1  "backup " 
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-backup \- Commands to create, schedule, inspect, and restore backups
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli backup\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Commands to create, schedule, inspect, and restore backups
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-activity(1)
Commands to inspect backup and restore activity
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-create(1)
Create a backup for all packages
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-estimate\-capacity(1)
Estimate automatic backup storage requirements
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-history(1)
Commands to inspect automatic backup checkpoint history
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-job(1)
Commands to manage automatic backup jobs
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-policy(1)
Commands to preview and apply automatic backup retention policies
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-review(1)
Commands to resolve automatic backup decisions for new services
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-target(1)
Commands related to a backup target
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-targets(1)
List existing backup targets
